    <h1>Emergency Checklist Guide</h1>
    <p>Comprehensive Disaster Preparedness for Students</p>
  </header>

  <!-- Page 1 -->
  <section>
    <h2>1. Stay Calm</h2>
    <p>Remain calm during any emergency. Panic can cause mistakes and delays.</p>
  </section>

  <!-- Page 2 -->
  <section>
    <h2>2. Alert an Adult</h2>
    <p>Immediately inform a teacher, parent, or responsible adult about the situation.</p>
  </section>

  <!-- Page 3 -->
  <section>
    <h2>3. Emergency Contacts</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Fire Brigade – 101</li>
      <li>Ambulance – 102</li>
      <li>Police – 100</li>
      <li>Emergency Helpline – 112</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <!-- Page 4 -->
  <section>
    <h2>4. Safe Place</h2>
    <p>Identify a safe location to assemble, such as a playground or open ground.</p>
  </section>

  <!-- Page 5 -->
  <section>
    <h2>5. Follow Instructions</h2>
    <p>Always listen to announcements and guidance from teachers or officials.</p>
  </section>

  <!-- Page 6 -->
  <section>
    <h2>6. Emergency Kit Essentials</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>First Aid Kit (bandages, antiseptic wipes, gauze)</li>
      <li>Whistle, flashlight, spare batteries</li>
      <li>Drinking water and snacks</li>
      <li>Identity card and emergency contact list</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <!-- Page 7 -->
  <section>
    <h2>7. Fire Safety</h2>
    <p>Stop, Drop, and Roll if clothes catch fire. Evacuate through nearest exits.</p>
  </section>

  <!-- Page 8 -->
  <section>
    <h2>8. Earthquake Safety</h2>
    <p>Drop, Cover, and Hold until the shaking stops. Stay away from windows.</p>
  </section>

  <!-- Page 9 -->
  <section>
    <h2>9. Flood Safety</h2>
    <p>Avoid floodwaters. Move to higher ground immediately.</p>
  </section>

  <!-- Page 10 -->
  <section>
    <h2>10. Gas Leak Precautions</h2>
    <p>Do not use electrical switches. Open windows and evacuate calmly.</p>
  </section>

  <!-- Page 11 -->
  <section>
    <h2>11. Severe Storm Safety</h2>
    <p>Stay indoors, away from glass windows. Keep emergency lights ready.</p>
  </section>

  <!-- Page 12 -->
  <section>
    <h2>12. Final Tips</h2>
    <p>Practice emergency drills regularly and update your emergency contacts.</p>
  </section>

